<p>Network data confirm the restriction of social media and messaging platforms Facebook, WhatsApp, Instagram and Messenger in Suriname from Friday evening 17 February 2023 local time. The incident came amid protests over the rising cost of living as protesters stormed the National Assembly. Access was restored on Saturday morning.</p>
